 consists of one [Mo3S4(NTA)3]5− cluster, two La3+ cations, one Cl− anion and lattice water molecules. The asymmetric unit contains three independent molybdenum atoms, labelled MoA, MoB, MoC and two La3+ cations (noted La1 and La2). The molybdenum atoms form the triangular core {Mo3S4} with classical bond lengths and angles (
) and each one is octahedrally coordinated by three sulphur atoms, one nitrogen atom and two oxygen atoms of one aminotriacetic ligand labelled respectively A, B and C. Each aminotriacetic ligand possesses three carboxylates functions. Each ligand shows a free carboxylate function labelled respectively A1, B1 and C1 and two carboxylate functions coordinated to one molybdenum atom labelled A2, A3, B2, B3 and C2, C3 (
